This paper is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category as it proposes a new method for improving value estimation in model-free reinforcement learning algorithms. It also incorporates learned dynamics models, which are a common topic in machine learning research. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as reinforcement learning is a subfield of AI and the paper proposes a new method for improving RL algorithms. 

cs.RO (Robotics) is another likely sub-category as RL is commonly used in robotics applications and the paper mentions continuous control tasks, which are often encountered in robotics. 

cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possibility as the paper deals with control and estimation in RL algorithms. 

Finally, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a less likely but still possible sub-category as the paper mentions the use of learned dynamics models, which are often used in computer vision applications.
